                            <comment id="15832306" author="githubbot" created="Fri, 20 Jan 2017 19:36:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;GitHub user zregvart opened a pull request:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/camel/pull/1414&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/camel/pull/1414&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-10732&quot; title=&quot;Remove from all caches when Groovy script is removed from Camel script cache&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CAMEL-10732&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CAMEL-10732&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; Remove from all caches when Groovy ...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    ...script is removed from Camel script cache&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    This commit wraps the `Class&amp;lt;Script&amp;gt;` in a `org.apache.camel.Service`&lt;br/&gt;
    before placing it in the cache so that on removal from the cache `stop`&lt;br/&gt;
    method would be invoked in which Groovy&apos;s `InvokerHelper` is used to&lt;br/&gt;
    cleanup three other caches that still hold references to the Script&lt;br/&gt;
    Class in question.&lt;/p&gt;

